<p><b>Greg Mortenson</b> (born 1957) is a <a href="/wiki/Humanitarianism" title="Humanitarianism">humanitarian</a>, international peace-maker, and former mountaineer from <a href="/wiki/Bozeman,_Montana" title="Bozeman, Montana">Bozeman</a>, <a href="/wiki/Montana" title="Montana">Montana</a>. Mortenson is the co-founder (with Dr. <a href="/wiki/Jean_Hoerni" title="Jean Hoerni">Jean Hoerni</a>) and director of the non-profit <a href="/wiki/Central_Asia_Institute" title="Central Asia Institute">Central Asia Institute</a>, and founder of the educational charity, <a href="/wiki/Pennies_for_Peace" title="Pennies for Peace">Pennies For Peace</a>. He is the protagonist and co-author of the # 1 <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a></i> bestseller, <i><a href="/wiki/Three_Cups_of_Tea" title="Three Cups of Tea">Three Cups of Tea</a>: One Man's Mission To Promote Peace... One School At A Time</i>.</p>
